- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the paper deals with radio networks and their implementation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another likely category as the paper presents randomized algorithms for leader election. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper deals with networks and their properties. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper presents algorithms with probabilistic guarantees.
